1
00:02:06,345 --> 00:02:09,065
…The person I thought would take my side

2
00:02:10,065 --> 00:02:11,585
and protect me

3
00:02:12,184 --> 00:02:13,945
turn against me like that.

4
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:15,665
I'm so sorry.

5
00:02:19,624 --> 00:02:20,745
Mutual understanding

6
00:02:21,344 --> 00:02:23,305
requires an open mind.

7
00:02:23,385 --> 00:02:25,184
When did you get so smart?

8
00:02:25,265 --> 00:02:26,505
Do you like it?

9
00:02:26,585 --> 00:02:27,585
I like it.

10
00:02:30,624 --> 00:02:32,305
What happened to you in the past

11
00:02:32,785 --> 00:02:34,545
made you lose faith in love,

12
00:02:34,624 --> 00:02:38,145
but I'm going to show you
how serious I am about you.

13
00:02:39,985 --> 00:02:41,665
-Mom!
-Mrs. Na.

14
00:02:47,425 --> 00:02:49,945
-Dress up tomorrow.
-Yes?

15
00:02:50,025 --> 00:02:51,585
We are going shopping tomorrow.

16
00:02:52,305 --> 00:02:53,305
Nut.

17
00:02:53,904 --> 00:02:56,425
This is Mr. Nobu.

18
00:02:56,505 --> 00:02:59,184
He wants to buy your show
and broadcast it in Japan.

19
00:03:00,705 --> 00:03:01,624
Hello.

20
00:03:01,705 --> 00:03:02,665
Hello.

21
00:03:05,665 --> 00:03:07,745
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you, too.

22
00:03:08,225 --> 00:03:10,385
I am from Tokyo. My name is Nobu.

23
00:03:11,105 --> 00:03:12,545
Please be kind to me.

24
00:03:13,184 --> 00:03:15,425
This is Mr. Yoshi.

25
00:03:15,504 --> 00:03:18,265
He is an entertainment reporter.
He's here to interview you.

26
00:03:19,705 --> 00:03:20,585
Nice to meet you.

27
00:03:22,825 --> 00:03:24,545
-Mr. Nobu.
-Yes?

28
00:03:24,624 --> 00:03:27,105
We will go and sign
the contract in my office.

29
00:03:27,784 --> 00:03:32,064
And leave Nut and Mr. Yoshi here
for the interview.

30
00:03:38,705 --> 00:03:40,745
-Mr. Nobu.
-Yes?

31
00:03:40,825 --> 00:03:42,504
Want some Japanese sake?

32
00:03:43,064 --> 00:03:45,344
I love sake.

33
00:03:45,425 --> 00:03:47,904
-Rice whiskey?
-Whiskey.

34
00:04:01,504 --> 00:04:02,825
Mrs. Na,

35
00:04:03,585 --> 00:04:05,425
Nut has not read it yet.

36
00:04:06,265 --> 00:04:07,665
He is probably busy.

37
00:04:09,705 --> 00:04:11,064
That’s all right.

38
00:04:11,145 --> 00:04:12,825
We can go by ourselves.

39
00:04:27,945 --> 00:04:29,264
How about these?

40
00:04:31,745 --> 00:04:33,785
They're a bit bright.

41
00:04:34,545 --> 00:04:36,745
People can see them from miles away.

42
00:04:37,785 --> 00:04:39,785
How about some plain ones?

43
00:04:42,345 --> 00:04:43,785
-Excuse me.
-Yes.

44
00:04:43,865 --> 00:04:45,305
Do you have other colors?

45
00:04:45,865 --> 00:04:47,545
We do. Please wait a moment.

46
00:04:56,945 --> 00:04:58,024
Do they fit well?

47
00:04:59,785 --> 00:05:01,745
They are a little tight.

48
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,625
-Miss.
-Yes?

49
00:05:05,704 --> 00:05:07,024
Do you have a bigger size?

50
00:05:07,105 --> 00:05:08,625
Of course. One moment please.

51
00:05:12,865 --> 00:05:14,704
I will take a look over there.

52
00:05:15,345 --> 00:05:16,345
Okay.

53
00:06:19,904 --> 00:06:21,505
Are they comfy?

54
00:06:35,264 --> 00:06:36,745
Try walking in them.

55
00:07:14,865 --> 00:07:16,225
Anything you like?

56
00:07:17,745 --> 00:07:20,225
They are all pretty. I can't pick one.

57
00:07:22,625 --> 00:07:24,425
Why don't we let Nut pick one for you?

58
00:07:25,385 --> 00:07:26,385
Shall we?

59
00:07:27,344 --> 00:07:28,344
Nut.

60
00:07:28,904 --> 00:07:30,625
Can you pick something for your mom?

61
00:08:18,824 --> 00:08:20,865
I told him

62
00:08:20,945 --> 00:08:22,464
that your phone is broken.

63
00:08:28,784 --> 00:08:30,024
What about this one?

64
00:08:30,625 --> 00:08:31,665
Would it suit Mom?

65
00:08:33,544 --> 00:08:34,784
It looks good.

66
00:08:39,664 --> 00:08:41,985
We should get the right color.

67
00:08:42,064 --> 00:08:43,745
I think she would like a pink one.

68
00:08:51,905 --> 00:08:53,304
Thank you, son.

69
00:09:05,265 --> 00:09:06,465
Let's go.

70
00:09:21,304 --> 00:09:22,705
What color would you like?

71
00:09:24,544 --> 00:09:27,145
The one that best suits my mom.

72
00:09:30,785 --> 00:09:32,985
Then I recommend this shade.

73
00:09:33,064 --> 00:09:34,064
It should suit you.

74
00:09:38,665 --> 00:09:39,825
Do you like it?

75
00:09:40,865 --> 00:09:42,265
How much is it?

76
00:09:42,345 --> 00:09:44,544
It is 599 baht.

77
00:09:47,985 --> 00:09:51,424
I stay home most of the time,
so I don't wear much makeup.

78
00:09:51,905 --> 00:09:53,745
You can look pretty at home too.

79
00:09:56,265 --> 00:09:59,184
Are they both your sons?
They're so handsome.

80
00:10:05,184 --> 00:10:06,184
Yes.

81
00:10:06,944 --> 00:10:08,304
He is my son.

82
00:10:11,465 --> 00:10:13,064
He is also my son.

83
00:10:17,705 --> 00:10:20,225
The three of us are a family.

84
00:10:26,025 --> 00:10:29,865
What about those two? Are they yours too?

85
00:10:29,944 --> 00:10:31,465
They've been looking over here.

86
00:10:33,825 --> 00:10:35,304
Song.

87
00:10:47,985 --> 00:10:49,424
Why are you following me?

88
00:10:50,105 --> 00:10:51,424
Who followed you?

89
00:10:51,505 --> 00:10:53,785
I was passing by and got a little curious.

90
00:10:54,505 --> 00:10:57,785
All this time, I have never seen you
go out with your mother.

91
00:10:57,865 --> 00:10:59,505
So I was wondering

92
00:10:59,585 --> 00:11:02,585
what has gotten into you today.

93
00:11:04,025 --> 00:11:05,505
Nothing much.

94
00:11:06,064 --> 00:11:08,064
I just brought my mom to the mall.

95
00:11:12,145 --> 00:11:15,145
I am glad you are happy.

96
00:11:16,745 --> 00:11:18,184
I've been waiting for this day.

97
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:27,145
What about you?

98
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:29,865
Why is he with you?

99
00:11:31,544 --> 00:11:33,705
You and he…

100
00:11:35,544 --> 00:11:36,944
Well, I…

101
00:11:41,345 --> 00:11:42,465
What about us?

102
00:11:42,544 --> 00:11:43,985
Well?

103
00:11:45,064 --> 00:11:46,064
So?

104
00:11:49,304 --> 00:11:50,585
This kid…

105
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:54,064
is not with me.

106
00:12:02,824 --> 00:12:04,225
It's me…

107
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:06,424
who is here with him.

108
00:12:09,424 --> 00:12:11,345
So, are you two together?

109
00:12:12,544 --> 00:12:14,905
Yes, as you can see.

110
00:12:16,265 --> 00:12:18,064
You said you didn't like younger guys.

111
00:12:19,585 --> 00:12:20,905
Did I?

112
00:12:20,985 --> 00:12:22,665
When was that? I can't recall.

113
00:12:27,785 --> 00:12:29,025
Well done.

114
00:12:29,585 --> 00:12:32,505
I will reward you with something later.

115
00:12:35,544 --> 00:12:36,824
You are the sweetest.

116
00:12:38,304 --> 00:12:41,465
Why aren’t we ordering something?
I'm hungry.

117
00:12:44,225 --> 00:12:46,505
Go for it, Tofu. Tell me what you want.

118
00:12:46,585 --> 00:12:50,064
Today, I am so happy
that I will treat you.

119
00:12:50,145 --> 00:12:52,064
-You said it.
-Of course.

120
00:12:52,145 --> 00:12:53,184
I'll order, then.

121
00:12:53,265 --> 00:12:54,785
Alright. Go ahead.

122
00:12:54,865 --> 00:12:56,824
-I want this one.
-This one?

123
00:12:56,905 --> 00:12:58,985
-And this.
-And this?

124
00:12:59,064 --> 00:13:00,785
-This one and this one.
-Those two?

125
00:13:00,865 --> 00:13:02,985
This one and this one. I want all of them.

126
00:13:03,064 --> 00:13:04,785
-Good job.
-All… all of them?

127
00:13:04,865 --> 00:13:06,184
Yes.

128
00:13:06,265 --> 00:13:07,505
You want all of them?

129
00:13:07,585 --> 00:13:08,745
Are you sure?

130
00:13:08,824 --> 00:13:10,385
-You said it was a treat.
-Really?

131
00:13:10,465 --> 00:13:11,944
-You said you would pay.
-I will.

132
00:13:12,025 --> 00:13:14,665
Eat what you like and I'll swipe my card.

133
00:13:36,184 --> 00:13:37,905
Hurry up and grow.

134
00:13:37,985 --> 00:13:39,665
There is a kid waiting to eat you.

135
00:13:41,184 --> 00:13:44,345
You're in a good mood today.

136
00:13:44,985 --> 00:13:47,625
You went on a date, right?
I saw Song earlier.

137
00:13:50,064 --> 00:13:52,105
I'm in a good mood because of Nut.

138
00:13:52,184 --> 00:13:56,304
I saw Nut. He took
his mom and Tofu shopping.

139
00:13:57,025 --> 00:13:58,745
Nut made up with his mom.

140
00:13:59,345 --> 00:14:00,544
Really?

141
00:14:03,145 --> 00:14:04,625
A lot of time was wasted though.

142
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:08,985
What I mean is…

143
00:14:09,064 --> 00:14:13,345
had they reconciled earlier,

144
00:14:13,424 --> 00:14:16,665
they would have spent
much more time together, right?

145
00:14:19,544 --> 00:14:21,265
You too, Gen.

146
00:14:21,345 --> 00:14:24,064
Don’t make love difficult.

147
00:14:24,625 --> 00:14:27,105
You never know what is going to happen.

148
00:14:27,665 --> 00:14:30,944
Be good to each other,
so you don’t regret it later.

149
00:14:33,225 --> 00:14:34,345
You know me.

150
00:14:34,424 --> 00:14:37,785
You are my son after all.
Of course, I know you.

151
00:15:18,385 --> 00:15:19,865
Thank you so much.

152
00:15:21,025 --> 00:15:23,424
I had a great time today, son.

153
00:15:49,225 --> 00:15:52,704
This has made becoming human worthwhile.

154
00:15:53,184 --> 00:15:54,785
At the very least,

155
00:15:54,865 --> 00:15:57,865
I get to help in healing the rift
between Nut and his mom.

156
00:16:22,865 --> 00:16:24,785
It made me realize

157
00:16:25,304 --> 00:16:27,905
that whether you are a mother or a child,

158
00:16:28,385 --> 00:16:30,184
everyone makes mistakes.

159
00:17:05,105 --> 00:17:06,264
I’m going, Mom.

160
00:17:14,224 --> 00:17:15,385
What about…

161
00:17:16,264 --> 00:17:17,305
my lunchbox?

162
00:17:27,464 --> 00:17:28,785
I'm going.

163
00:17:29,345 --> 00:17:30,385
All right.

164
00:17:37,065 --> 00:17:39,905
By accepting each other’s flaws

165
00:17:40,585 --> 00:17:42,865
with love and understanding,

166
00:17:43,905 --> 00:17:45,905
only then can the void be filled.

167
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:48,705
Seeing this

168
00:17:49,305 --> 00:17:51,225
has been worth it,

169
00:17:53,225 --> 00:17:54,504
even if

170
00:17:55,545 --> 00:17:57,504
I might be gone forever one day.

171
00:18:01,425 --> 00:18:03,264
You're here early, Gen.

172
00:18:03,345 --> 00:18:04,744
You are late.

173
00:18:14,585 --> 00:18:17,024
Hey, Gen. Let go.

174
00:18:18,465 --> 00:18:20,425
You're suddenly so possessive.

175
00:18:21,585 --> 00:18:24,264
-Won't you share anymore?
-No.

176
00:18:25,425 --> 00:18:27,024
It's a good thing Prib isn't here.

177
00:18:27,105 --> 00:18:28,705
Or else she would ask you for some.

178
00:18:29,425 --> 00:18:30,425
You are right.

179
00:18:31,065 --> 00:18:32,625
Where is my niece?

180
00:18:38,385 --> 00:18:40,625
Kuenchai.

181
00:18:41,305 --> 00:18:42,225
Why are you barking?

182
00:18:46,585 --> 00:18:47,625
Prib?

183
00:18:48,185 --> 00:18:49,744
I need to talk to you.

184
00:18:54,545 --> 00:18:56,865
Do you know Tatarn?

185
00:18:57,905 --> 00:18:59,665
Do you know him too?

186
00:19:00,625 --> 00:19:02,185
Did Nut tell you about him?

187
00:19:04,264 --> 00:19:06,504
Nut told me about his ex.

188
00:19:07,185 --> 00:19:08,625
He never told me the name.

189
00:19:09,865 --> 00:19:12,065
I found out his name is Tatarn.

190
00:19:13,465 --> 00:19:15,984
You are friends with him on Facebook.

191
00:19:18,825 --> 00:19:20,865
Can you take me to see him?

192
00:19:21,585 --> 00:19:23,345
I have to ask him something.

193
00:19:23,905 --> 00:19:25,585
I would like to,

194
00:19:26,225 --> 00:19:30,425
but Tarn is in a coma and has not been
responsive for months now.

195
00:19:32,385 --> 00:19:35,105
I really shouldn’t tell you this

196
00:19:35,185 --> 00:19:37,705
as it might be hard for you.

197
00:19:39,185 --> 00:19:41,425
But this is a really important matter.

198
00:19:43,024 --> 00:19:45,305
I want Nut to visit Tarn.

199
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:48,665
A miracle could happen.

200
00:19:49,545 --> 00:19:51,024
Even if it doesn't,

201
00:19:51,504 --> 00:19:52,744
at least,

202
00:19:53,305 --> 00:19:55,984
Tarn gets to see Nut one last time.

203
00:19:57,625 --> 00:19:59,784
Can you help me just this once?

204
00:20:03,585 --> 00:20:05,744
I've heard people say

205
00:20:06,504 --> 00:20:08,225
that happiness often doesn’t last.

206
00:20:18,145 --> 00:20:20,425
It is actually my secret,

207
00:20:21,465 --> 00:20:23,425
but I will tell you about it.

208
00:20:24,145 --> 00:20:26,385
Before I was into Nut,

209
00:20:26,465 --> 00:20:28,305
I used to like Tarn.

210
00:20:29,425 --> 00:20:32,024
It's a small world sometimes, Tofu.

211
00:20:32,625 --> 00:20:36,585
Two people I liked used to be in love.

212
00:20:37,905 --> 00:20:41,545
And that’s also why I want to help Tarn.

213
00:20:46,425 --> 00:20:49,345
That's why Tarn asked you
to draw him with Nut.

214
00:20:51,465 --> 00:20:55,385
He never mentioned Nut
in that page or on Facebook,

215
00:20:58,225 --> 00:20:59,784
but I can tell

216
00:21:01,385 --> 00:21:03,305
from all those photos and messages

217
00:21:04,305 --> 00:21:06,024
that he wanted Nut to know.

218
00:21:11,504 --> 00:21:13,225
Tarn still loves Nut, doesn't he?

219
00:21:16,264 --> 00:21:18,264
I don’t know about that.

220
00:21:18,744 --> 00:21:20,865
All I know is that

221
00:21:20,945 --> 00:21:23,625
Tarn never wanted to trouble Nut.

222
00:21:24,145 --> 00:21:27,504
Tarn told me
that he wanted Nut to be happy.

223
00:21:27,585 --> 00:21:29,625
He wants him to do the job he loves

224
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:31,945
and be surrounded by good people.

225
00:21:32,825 --> 00:21:34,625
And what happened between them

226
00:21:35,145 --> 00:21:39,145
should just be left as a happy memory.

227
00:21:41,504 --> 00:21:44,225
Isn’t that obvious?

228
00:21:47,744 --> 00:21:49,504
If he is still in love with Nut,

229
00:21:50,865 --> 00:21:52,905
why didn’t he come back for him?

230
00:21:54,665 --> 00:21:55,984
I know why.

231
00:21:59,145 --> 00:22:00,385
What did you just say?

232
00:22:00,905 --> 00:22:01,905
Well,

233
00:22:02,705 --> 00:22:04,425
you were wondering

234
00:22:04,504 --> 00:22:06,264
why they didn’t get back together.

235
00:22:08,625 --> 00:22:12,984
I think the guy is not sure
if the girl wants him back.

236
00:22:13,825 --> 00:22:15,465
Though they used to love each other

237
00:22:15,945 --> 00:22:17,585
and they broke up out of necessity,

238
00:22:18,504 --> 00:22:20,504
no one stays the same forever.

239
00:22:21,425 --> 00:22:23,784
Now that the girl has feelings
for that other guy,

240
00:22:24,585 --> 00:22:26,905
the guy who has been waiting

241
00:22:26,984 --> 00:22:28,105
is now afraid to act.

242
00:22:33,065 --> 00:22:34,145
Well…

243
00:22:35,185 --> 00:22:37,585
How do you think it will end?

244
00:22:38,945 --> 00:22:40,264
Just wait and see.

