Can you smell something burning?

273
00:25:02,385 --> 00:25:03,825
Tofu!

274
00:25:03,905 --> 00:25:05,825
You're miles away. It's burnt.

275
00:25:07,305 --> 00:25:08,304
Oh, gosh.

276
00:25:19,304 --> 00:25:20,345
Hey.

277
00:25:25,905 --> 00:25:26,984
Jeez!

278
00:25:27,625 --> 00:25:29,665
How am I supposed to eat that?

279
00:25:31,665 --> 00:25:33,264
Don't eat it if you don’t want to.

280
00:25:34,665 --> 00:25:37,105
I thought you wanted fried pork,
so I made some.

281
00:25:37,185 --> 00:25:38,544
If it's that bad,

282
00:25:39,024 --> 00:25:40,744
then get someone else to cook for you.

283
00:25:42,465 --> 00:25:44,065
I will give this to Kuenchai.

284
00:25:45,385 --> 00:25:46,665
Kuenchai, come here.

285
00:25:48,744 --> 00:25:49,744
Here.

286
00:25:56,465 --> 00:25:57,465
Eat it.

287
00:26:10,304 --> 00:26:11,744
What is it, boys?

288
00:26:12,665 --> 00:26:14,225
It's nothing, Mrs. Na.

289
00:26:14,304 --> 00:26:16,264
I burnt the fried pork.

290
00:26:17,225 --> 00:26:18,905
I’m heading to the market.

291
00:26:39,665 --> 00:26:41,585
I get Nut now, Kuenchai.

292
00:26:43,225 --> 00:26:45,625
I didn’t mean to be unreasonable.

293
00:26:46,665 --> 00:26:48,504
I couldn't help it.

294
00:26:55,945 --> 00:26:57,625
I lost, Kuenchai.

295
00:26:58,225 --> 00:27:00,145
I couldn't compete with him.

296
00:27:05,385 --> 00:27:06,425
Maybe…

297
00:27:07,784 --> 00:27:09,625
I should just tell him.

298
00:27:10,105 --> 00:27:11,425
Tell me what?

299
00:27:25,705 --> 00:27:27,264
I thought you went to the market.

300
00:27:31,865 --> 00:27:33,385
I didn't make it that far.

301
00:27:43,905 --> 00:27:45,385
What did you want to tell me?

302
00:27:49,625 --> 00:27:51,145
I was going to say…

303
00:27:59,385 --> 00:28:00,665
I’m sorry.

304
00:28:02,304 --> 00:28:04,145
I don’t know what's up with me.

305
00:28:08,625 --> 00:28:09,744
I know.

306
00:28:12,585 --> 00:28:13,984
How did you know?

307
00:28:14,585 --> 00:28:15,984
Because I’m the best.

308
00:28:16,825 --> 00:28:19,504
I’m your boyfriend,

309
00:28:19,585 --> 00:28:21,065
so I know what you are thinking.

310
00:28:30,825 --> 00:28:32,544
Don’t make that face.

311
00:28:32,625 --> 00:28:34,345
People will say I'm picking on a kid.

312
00:28:35,425 --> 00:28:37,425
Stop overthinking.

313
00:28:39,544 --> 00:28:43,264
I don’t know if I did something that made
you feel insecure.

314
00:28:44,585 --> 00:28:46,225
I will tell you this one more time.

315
00:28:47,185 --> 00:28:48,625
You are you,

316
00:28:49,744 --> 00:28:51,544
and I love that about you.

317
00:29:02,905 --> 00:29:04,905
I didn’t want to feel this way.

318
00:29:06,744 --> 00:29:08,585
I just can’t help it.

319
00:29:10,984 --> 00:29:12,705
Let me stay like this a bit longer.

320
00:29:14,744 --> 00:29:16,744
What’s the matter with you, Tofu?

321
00:29:18,744 --> 00:29:20,625
If I’m unreasonable like this again,

322
00:29:21,345 --> 00:29:23,145
will you still love me?

323
00:29:25,185 --> 00:29:27,145
I’m like that all the time,

324
00:29:28,145 --> 00:29:29,304
and you still love me.

325
00:29:39,984 --> 00:29:41,145
What if…

326
00:29:43,304 --> 00:29:45,465
you meet someone better than me,

327
00:29:46,105 --> 00:29:48,504
someone you are happier with,

328
00:29:50,145 --> 00:29:52,425
and isn't a burden like me?

329
00:29:54,105 --> 00:29:55,744
Will you leave me for him?

330
00:29:58,225 --> 00:29:59,345
All right.

331
00:29:59,865 --> 00:30:01,744
Even if you always burn the pork,

332
00:30:02,264 --> 00:30:03,585
I won’t leave you.

333
00:30:04,064 --> 00:30:05,264
Are you satisfied?

334
00:30:11,345 --> 00:30:12,585
I promise

335
00:30:13,264 --> 00:30:15,544
that I won’t give you cancer.

336
00:30:17,145 --> 00:30:20,185
I will fry the pork beautifully next time.

337
00:30:22,544 --> 00:30:23,825
I'll make it like

338
00:30:25,744 --> 00:30:26,984
how you used to have it.

339
00:30:30,865 --> 00:30:34,105
When did I ever tell you
that the fried pork I used to eat

340
00:30:35,064 --> 00:30:36,264
was so good?

341
00:30:38,984 --> 00:30:40,625
Where did you get this from?

342
00:30:41,385 --> 00:30:43,385
Why do you ask? Do you want some?

343
00:30:43,865 --> 00:30:46,665
I only asked where you got it,

344
00:30:46,744 --> 00:30:48,185
so that I won’t eat there.

345
00:30:48,744 --> 00:30:50,425
I made it myself.

346
00:30:50,504 --> 00:30:52,345
It might not look great,

347
00:30:53,264 --> 00:30:54,544
but it tastes amazing.

348
00:30:55,264 --> 00:30:56,504
Want to try it?

349
00:30:57,425 --> 00:30:58,784
Yuck.

350
00:30:58,865 --> 00:31:01,024
Try it. I put a lot of effort into it.

351
00:31:01,504 --> 00:31:02,504
Here.

352
00:31:05,264 --> 00:31:06,264
How is it?

353
00:31:07,145 --> 00:31:08,185
Delicious, right?

354
00:31:08,784 --> 00:31:09,784
Hey,

355
00:31:10,345 --> 00:31:11,425
it's great.

356
00:31:12,625 --> 00:31:16,345
If you want more,
then eat with me every day.

357
00:31:16,425 --> 00:31:18,185
I live alone.

358
00:31:18,264 --> 00:31:21,064
How about I make you Thai barbecue

359
00:31:22,504 --> 00:31:23,744
over at my condo?

360
00:31:26,504 --> 00:31:27,825
It looked…

361
00:31:29,504 --> 00:31:31,585
It looked just like the stuff you made.

362
00:31:33,145 --> 00:31:35,345
It was all in your head
and you blamed me for it.

363
00:31:36,504 --> 00:31:40,024
Don’t get all upset
about me remembering it.

364
00:31:41,504 --> 00:31:45,585
It was just one of the first times
we ate together. That's all.

365
00:31:48,705 --> 00:31:51,264
Do you remember
the first time we ate together?

366
00:31:52,945 --> 00:31:55,544
Are you looking for something
to argue about, Tofu?

367
00:31:58,784 --> 00:32:01,304
Stop comparing yourself with someone else.

368
00:32:02,024 --> 00:32:03,544
Be confident in yourself.

369
00:32:07,504 --> 00:32:09,145
And trust me.

370
00:32:18,705 --> 00:32:21,225
You said you wanted me
to be patient with you.

371
00:32:23,225 --> 00:32:25,504
You should be patient with me too.

372
00:32:27,385 --> 00:32:28,905
I promise

373
00:32:29,984 --> 00:32:31,705
that I won’t be like this…

374
00:32:32,865 --> 00:32:34,225
too often.

375
00:32:36,784 --> 00:32:38,064
Tofu.

376
00:33:05,544 --> 00:33:08,544
THE LITTLE PRINCE

377
00:33:20,385 --> 00:33:21,905
Where have you been?

378
00:33:22,465 --> 00:33:24,064
Did you get the pork?

379
00:33:25,064 --> 00:33:26,865
I’m sorry I made you worry.

380
00:33:27,465 --> 00:33:30,425
Also, I didn’t get any pork.

381
00:33:32,585 --> 00:33:33,784
That’s fine.

382
00:33:33,865 --> 00:33:37,304
Never mind. Nhong brought
some stir-fried rice noodles he made.

383
00:33:39,425 --> 00:33:40,744
I'll set the table.

384
00:33:41,264 --> 00:33:42,625
Let me help you.

385
00:34:06,225 --> 00:34:07,984
I'll pour the water.

386
00:34:12,904 --> 00:34:15,344
THE LITTLE PRINCE

387
00:34:15,424 --> 00:34:16,264
THE LITTLE PRINCE

388
00:34:25,065 --> 00:34:27,864
Is your work done?
You're checking holiday spots.

389
00:34:28,505 --> 00:34:32,025
Do you want me to only work
and ignore Mom and you?

390
00:34:32,585 --> 00:34:33,665
Would you like that?

391
00:34:33,744 --> 00:34:34,744
No.

392
00:34:36,545 --> 00:34:38,225
Don’t tell me

393
00:34:38,304 --> 00:34:40,065
that you're taking us on holiday.

394
00:34:41,264 --> 00:34:42,304
Yes.

395
00:34:43,705 --> 00:34:46,545
I saw Mom reading The Little Prince
over and over.

396
00:34:47,424 --> 00:34:49,465
She might want to travel like he did.

397
00:34:50,185 --> 00:34:52,744
You guys will go out of your minds
just staying at home.

398
00:34:52,824 --> 00:34:54,304
Let's take a trip and relax.

399
00:34:58,065 --> 00:34:59,185
This time,

400
00:35:00,185 --> 00:35:01,825
we'll go as a family.

401
00:35:02,785 --> 00:35:04,505
We can go as a couple next time.

402
00:35:05,345 --> 00:35:06,384
Deal.

403
00:35:08,465 --> 00:35:11,305
Help me pick a place.
Where should I take Mom?

404
00:35:12,105 --> 00:35:14,105
We haven't been anywhere together
for ages.

405
00:35:15,145 --> 00:35:16,505
Well…

406
00:35:17,145 --> 00:35:19,985
How about we ask your mom?

407
00:35:21,424 --> 00:35:23,065
-Do you think so?
-Yes.

408
00:35:25,705 --> 00:35:28,145
I don't mind. You decide.

409
00:35:29,065 --> 00:35:30,345
See? I told you.

410
00:35:31,465 --> 00:35:34,785
You are her son.
Of course, you know what she thinks.

411
00:35:36,505 --> 00:35:38,145
If Mom won’t choose,

412
00:35:38,225 --> 00:35:39,505
then I'll let you choose.

413
00:35:41,665 --> 00:35:42,625
Where shall we go?

414
00:35:43,505 --> 00:35:44,585
I can choose?

415
00:35:48,305 --> 00:35:49,904
I want to go to Chiang Mai.

416
00:35:57,625 --> 00:35:59,424
What is it, Kuenchai?

417
00:35:59,985 --> 00:36:01,505
Don't give me that look.

418
00:36:01,585 --> 00:36:03,025
You don’t get to go.

419
00:36:03,105 --> 00:36:04,384
Stay home.

420
00:36:20,465 --> 00:36:26,944
TOFU: NUT, MRS. NA AND I
ARE GOING TO CHIANG MAI.

421
00:36:30,185 --> 00:36:35,424
PRIBPREE: SORRY I GAVE YOU A HARD TIME,
TOFU. I WAS BEING SELFISH, WASN'T I?

422
00:36:44,305 --> 00:36:49,465
TOFU: EVERYONE CAN BE SELFISH,
ME INCLUDED.

423
00:37:06,985 --> 00:37:09,345
I didn't promise Prib anything.

424
00:37:09,904 --> 00:37:12,864
Maybe not,
but you're dragging Nut to Chiang Mai.

425
00:37:12,944 --> 00:37:15,785
I want to see if you can stand
not telling Nut about it.

426
00:37:17,545 --> 00:37:19,705
I know this is important.

427
00:37:19,785 --> 00:37:21,785
It is a matter of life and death,

428
00:37:22,745 --> 00:37:24,545
but I don’t want to tell him about it.

429
00:37:25,545 --> 00:37:26,625
I’m afraid.

430
00:37:27,185 --> 00:37:30,145
Humans need to be
a little selfish sometimes

431
00:37:30,225 --> 00:37:32,585
in order to avoid getting hurt too badly.

432
00:37:35,025 --> 00:37:36,985
I don’t want to be that kind of human.

433
00:37:37,785 --> 00:37:40,825
They are so fearful, dishonest,

434
00:37:41,545 --> 00:37:42,904
envious,

435
00:37:43,424 --> 00:37:45,065
and even jealous.

436
00:37:45,145 --> 00:37:49,105
That is because you are in love.

437
00:37:49,185 --> 00:37:52,625
You'll learn more about life as you grow.

438
00:37:52,705 --> 00:37:56,384
I know Nut
will always be there to help you.

439
00:38:03,985 --> 00:38:05,185
Tofu.

440
00:38:05,864 --> 00:38:07,145
Why aren't you packing?

441
00:38:08,265 --> 00:38:09,825
We’re leaving tomorrow.

442
00:38:11,785 --> 00:38:12,944
Here.

443
00:38:13,825 --> 00:38:14,825
What’s wrong?

444
00:38:15,384 --> 00:38:16,464
I'm tired.

445
00:38:29,785 --> 00:38:30,985
Well…

446
00:38:31,065 --> 00:38:32,585
This trip is kind of sudden.

447
00:38:33,305 --> 00:38:34,705
Are you sure Juea won't mind?

448
00:38:35,345 --> 00:38:37,025
Why would he mind?

449
00:38:37,105 --> 00:38:39,424
I worked day and night
to finish the script.

450
00:38:39,505 --> 00:38:40,825
He has a lot to work on.

451
00:38:42,105 --> 00:38:43,305
What about Gen?

452
00:38:49,225 --> 00:38:50,864
Can you go pack now?

453
00:38:53,265 --> 00:38:55,785
I can’t. I’m exhausted.

454
00:39:02,745 --> 00:39:03,944
Do you feel better now?

455
00:39:13,345 --> 00:39:14,665
Nut is going to Chiang Mai.

456
00:39:15,665 --> 00:39:16,864
Right.

457
00:39:16,944 --> 00:39:19,105
He said he is taking his family on a trip.

458
00:39:19,665 --> 00:39:22,065
-I see.
-So what?

459
00:39:22,145 --> 00:39:23,705
I’m envious.

460
00:39:23,785 --> 00:39:25,665
I haven’t taken a vacation in ages.

461
00:39:26,785 --> 00:39:28,185
Then take the vacation now.

462
00:39:28,944 --> 00:39:30,745
And I'm going with you.

463
00:39:30,825 --> 00:39:31,985
Hey.

464
00:39:32,545 --> 00:39:33,505
Here to deliver food?

465
00:39:34,825 --> 00:39:35,904
No.

466
00:39:35,985 --> 00:39:37,864
I’m here to see my boyfriend.

467
00:39:41,225 --> 00:39:42,424
I'm just kidding.

468
00:39:42,505 --> 00:39:43,904
I’m here to pick up my check.

469
00:39:46,665 --> 00:39:48,025
What are you talking about?

470
00:39:48,985 --> 00:39:51,705
Well, Nut is going to Chiang Mai.

471
00:39:51,785 --> 00:39:53,305
Gen wants to go too,

472
00:39:54,025 --> 00:39:56,545
so I’m going to take him there.

473
00:39:56,625 --> 00:39:58,305
We can go and see my dad too.

474
00:40:00,265 --> 00:40:01,464
Who said I’m going?

475
00:40:02,065 --> 00:40:03,225
I’m going.

476
00:40:25,145 --> 00:40:26,424
Who's that?

477
00:40:30,985 --> 00:40:32,065
Hello?

478
00:40:35,384 --> 00:40:36,384
Tofu.

479
00:40:40,345 --> 00:40:42,145
What's taking you so long?

480
00:40:42,785 --> 00:40:45,625
You seem more excited than me.

481
00:40:46,464 --> 00:40:48,265
You talk too much.

482
00:40:48,345 --> 00:40:49,864
Go pack your suitcase.

483
00:40:50,705 --> 00:40:51,745
Go.

484
00:41:05,345 --> 00:41:06,904
Is anyone there?

485
00:41:22,585 --> 00:41:24,505
Keep an eye on the house for us.

486
00:41:24,585 --> 00:41:28,585
-Okay.
-Don't worry. We'll tend to your house.

487
00:41:28,665 --> 00:41:32,065
If something happens, give me a call.

488
00:41:32,145 --> 00:41:33,745
Thank you so much.

489
00:41:33,825 --> 00:41:36,985
No problem. Have a good trip.

490
00:41:37,545 --> 00:41:40,985
I hope you all have a great time.

491
00:41:41,065 --> 00:41:42,065
Okay.

492
00:41:42,545 --> 00:41:45,145
Where is Kuenchai?

493
00:41:45,705 --> 00:41:47,464
Is he going too?

494
00:41:48,265 --> 00:41:49,545
-Hey.
-Hey.

495
00:41:50,105 --> 00:41:51,825
He's in the car.

496
00:41:51,904 --> 00:41:53,185
Kuenchai.

497
00:41:53,265 --> 00:41:54,625
He probably wants to go.

498
00:41:54,705 --> 00:41:57,265
-There he is.
-You can't go. Come here.

499
00:41:57,345 --> 00:41:58,625
There he is.

500
00:42:00,904 --> 00:42:02,185
-Kuenchai.
-Kuenchai.

501
00:42:04,265 --> 00:42:06,464
Hey.

502
00:42:06,545 --> 00:42:08,145
Kuenchai. Come here, boy.

503
00:42:08,225 --> 00:42:09,745
Sit.

504
00:42:09,825 --> 00:42:12,345
Be a good boy, all right?

505
00:42:12,424 --> 00:42:14,025
I’ll be back soon. Okay?

506
00:42:14,105 --> 00:42:15,745
Be good.

507
00:42:15,825 --> 00:42:17,384
Don't be a bad boy.

508
00:42:17,464 --> 00:42:18,985
-Let's go.
-Kuenchai.

509
00:42:19,825 --> 00:42:21,864
-Nhong.
-Sorry to bother you.

510
00:42:21,944 --> 00:42:24,825
-Come here.
-Kuenchai, sit.

511
00:42:24,904 --> 00:42:26,384
Here, turn that way.

512
00:42:26,464 --> 00:42:28,585
I’m sorry we can’t take you with us.

513
00:42:28,665 --> 00:42:30,105
I'll buy you some treats, okay?

514
00:42:32,384 --> 00:42:33,345
Have fun.

515
00:42:34,505 --> 00:42:36,185
Shall we go?

516
00:42:36,265 --> 00:42:37,384
Let’s go.

517
00:42:37,464 --> 00:42:39,785
Thanks for your help. Take care.

518
00:42:39,864 --> 00:42:41,424
-Goodbye.
-Have a safe trip.

519
00:42:41,505 --> 00:42:43,745
-Thank you.
-Bye, Kuenchai.

520
00:42:43,825 --> 00:42:47,545
-Bye.
-Bye. Be good.

521
00:42:47,625 --> 00:42:50,345
-Wave goodbye.
-Bye.

522
00:43:43,145 --> 00:43:44,424
It’s beautiful.

523
00:44:05,665 --> 00:44:07,305
Oh, wow.

524
00:44:08,864 --> 00:44:10,145
Nut.

525
00:44:10,225 --> 00:44:12,785
What's up, bro?

526
00:44:12,864 --> 00:44:15,145
-Hello.
-Hello.

527
00:44:15,825 --> 00:44:17,464
How was the drive? Are you tired?

528
00:44:18,105 --> 00:44:19,145
Why are you so hyper?

529
00:44:20,545 --> 00:44:21,984
Are you tired, Mrs. Na?

530
00:44:22,065 --> 00:44:23,345
Just a little.

531
00:44:23,424 --> 00:44:24,545
Well, well…

532
00:44:24,625 --> 00:44:27,505
You don’t look like someone
who has just traveled for ten hours.

533
00:44:28,065 --> 00:44:29,265
I’m envious.

534
00:44:29,345 --> 00:44:30,904
I want to take a road trip too.

535
00:44:34,625 --> 00:44:36,785
-I'm going to check in.
-All right.

536
00:44:37,345 --> 00:44:38,265
Mom, Tofu, let’s go.

537
00:44:38,345 --> 00:44:40,864
-Do you need me?
-Of course. We need your ID card.

538
00:44:42,904 --> 00:44:44,424
Coming by plane is better.

539
00:44:44,505 --> 00:44:47,105
Your food delivery motorbike
is not a big bike.

540
00:44:47,185 --> 00:44:49,225
Even if it were, I wouldn't ride with you.

541
00:44:49,305 --> 00:44:51,825
You might get weird and take orders
along the way.

542
00:44:52,585 --> 00:44:54,505
I could drive your car here.

543
00:44:54,585 --> 00:44:56,145
Why trouble yourself driving?

544
00:44:56,225 --> 00:44:58,185
Just enjoy the trip, all right?

545
00:44:58,944 --> 00:45:02,305
We get it. You care about Song.

546
00:45:03,225 --> 00:45:04,065
Are we done?

547
00:45:04,145 --> 00:45:06,705
