-Nut.

563
00:46:23,384 --> 00:46:24,745
That's a great picture.

564
00:46:36,904 --> 00:46:38,384
Can we go inside?

565
00:46:51,345 --> 00:46:52,705
Song. Come here.

566
00:47:10,384 --> 00:47:12,464
Your mom looks so happy.

567
00:47:15,384 --> 00:47:17,464
She's a history teacher after all.

568
00:47:18,625 --> 00:47:20,825
When I was little,
she used to read me stories.

569
00:47:21,384 --> 00:47:23,545
When we had finished them all,

570
00:47:24,145 --> 00:47:28,145
she then told me stories
about Thai history and foreign history.

571
00:47:29,785 --> 00:47:31,065
How nice.

572
00:47:31,984 --> 00:47:33,505
I want to hear them too.

573
00:47:34,705 --> 00:47:36,625
Can you tell me some stories at bedtime?

574
00:47:37,904 --> 00:47:39,345
Go ask my mother.

575
00:47:39,864 --> 00:47:41,745
I don’t like history like she does.

576
00:47:43,265 --> 00:47:44,345
Why not?

577
00:47:45,984 --> 00:47:48,025
History depends on who's writing it.

578
00:47:48,944 --> 00:47:51,145
It's what you choose to believe.

579
00:47:52,225 --> 00:47:54,105
We like to believe in what we agree with.

580
00:47:55,265 --> 00:47:57,505
A lot of people use belief as a weapon

581
00:47:58,145 --> 00:48:00,185
to hurt those who think differently.

582
00:48:01,585 --> 00:48:03,785
Some use it as a tool hiding the truth

583
00:48:04,265 --> 00:48:06,464
to serve their purpose.

584
00:48:09,065 --> 00:48:11,585
The same way my parents used to tell me

585
00:48:12,944 --> 00:48:15,265
that being who I am is a sin.

586
00:48:19,705 --> 00:48:21,145
When I grew up,

587
00:48:22,105 --> 00:48:23,305
I realized

588
00:48:23,384 --> 00:48:25,025
that there are other beliefs

589
00:48:25,585 --> 00:48:27,305
that no one else had told me…

590
00:48:29,464 --> 00:48:30,665
except…

591
00:48:34,785 --> 00:48:36,424
Tatarn, right?

592
00:48:40,585 --> 00:48:41,585
Yes.

593
00:48:43,904 --> 00:48:46,424
He was the one who made me understand

594
00:48:46,505 --> 00:48:48,065
that being gay isn't a disease.

595
00:48:48,705 --> 00:48:50,065
It's not down to bad karma,

596
00:48:51,384 --> 00:48:52,904
or an emotional disorder.

597
00:48:53,864 --> 00:48:55,825
And it's not a joke.

598
00:48:57,065 --> 00:48:58,585
Being gay

599
00:48:58,665 --> 00:49:01,225
doesn't mean we love every one
of the same gender.

600
00:49:02,145 --> 00:49:05,025
We can love someone
as sincerely as anyone else.

601
00:49:11,225 --> 00:49:13,505
That’s why I became a writer.

602
00:49:14,625 --> 00:49:16,585
I want to use my stories as a weapon

603
00:49:17,065 --> 00:49:19,025
and erase those wrong beliefs.

604
00:49:21,225 --> 00:49:23,545
You really are your mother’s son.

605
00:49:24,265 --> 00:49:26,185
She likes to tell stories.

606
00:49:26,265 --> 00:49:28,225
You also have something to tell.

607
00:49:29,185 --> 00:49:30,665
Perhaps

608
00:49:30,745 --> 00:49:33,145
her history lessons

609
00:49:33,665 --> 00:49:36,665
motivated you to become a writer.

610
00:49:37,225 --> 00:49:39,944
I’m sorry, Nut.
I got carried away walking around.

611
00:49:41,505 --> 00:49:42,785
Where are we going next?

612
00:49:45,585 --> 00:49:46,944
Where do you want to go?

613
00:49:47,025 --> 00:49:48,384
It's up to you.

614
00:49:49,625 --> 00:49:51,105
You want me to decide?

615
00:49:55,825 --> 00:49:57,065
Oh, wow.

616
00:49:57,665 --> 00:49:59,424
You wanted to come here?

617
00:50:02,225 --> 00:50:04,105
I never thought I would get to come here.

618
00:50:07,825 --> 00:50:11,185
I never knew you would like
something so extreme.

619
00:50:14,864 --> 00:50:17,145
I've always wanted to give it a try.

620
00:50:30,145 --> 00:50:31,145
Smile!

621
00:51:31,545 --> 00:51:33,025
Nut!

622
00:51:44,745 --> 00:51:45,944
That was fun.

623
00:51:46,864 --> 00:51:48,705
Are you all right, Tofu?

624
00:51:49,904 --> 00:51:51,625
Are you all right, Tofu?

625
00:51:52,944 --> 00:51:54,265
I'm fine.

626
00:51:54,345 --> 00:51:56,145
Can we go somewhere less exciting next?

627
00:51:58,185 --> 00:51:59,265
I knew it.

628
00:51:59,745 --> 00:52:02,345
Nut has finally fulfilled his mom's dream.

629
00:52:05,384 --> 00:52:08,705
If you want to go somewhere, just tell me.

630
00:52:09,185 --> 00:52:10,305
I will take you there.

631
00:52:12,305 --> 00:52:14,785
I’m glad I got
to take a trip with you before…

632
00:52:16,305 --> 00:52:17,625
while I still can.

633
00:52:20,864 --> 00:52:22,785
You are still healthy, Mrs. Na.

634
00:52:22,864 --> 00:52:25,384
You still have enough time to travel
the world with Nut.

635
00:52:26,625 --> 00:52:28,944
It’s just that he's probably too busy
to take you.

636
00:52:29,025 --> 00:52:31,625
Wrong. I can't afford it.

637
00:52:31,705 --> 00:52:34,185
Being a writer doesn't make you rich.

638
00:52:36,265 --> 00:52:39,185
But actors like me are quite rich.

639
00:52:39,265 --> 00:52:41,904
I can take you to travel the world
many times.

640
00:52:41,984 --> 00:52:44,424
You are rich, are you? So rich?

641
00:52:45,625 --> 00:52:46,984
I think,

642
00:52:47,065 --> 00:52:48,345
for the next place,

643
00:52:49,105 --> 00:52:50,665
let's go somewhere Tofu will like.

644
00:52:52,745 --> 00:52:53,864
All right.

645
00:52:54,545 --> 00:52:56,065
I know the perfect place.

646
00:53:03,745 --> 00:53:06,105
How is this a place for Tofu?

647
00:53:07,904 --> 00:53:10,225
Why? You don't think it suits him?

648
00:53:11,384 --> 00:53:15,145
She probably wondered why it suits Tofu
better than her.

649
00:53:15,705 --> 00:53:18,545
Gen, I was just curious.

650
00:53:19,105 --> 00:53:22,225
Flowers don't have to be for girls only.

651
00:53:22,305 --> 00:53:24,625
They can also go well with men.
Right, Mrs. Na?

652
00:53:24,705 --> 00:53:26,944
That's right.

653
00:53:27,785 --> 00:53:29,745
I remember wondering

654
00:53:29,825 --> 00:53:33,345
why people associated flowers
with one gender.

655
00:53:33,904 --> 00:53:36,745
When we give someone flowers,

656
00:53:36,825 --> 00:53:40,504
no one tells us the gender of each flower
or who are they suitable for.

657
00:53:40,585 --> 00:53:43,145
We give someone flowers because we know

658
00:53:43,225 --> 00:53:45,585
their meaning
and the reason we give them to someone.

659
00:53:46,145 --> 00:53:47,825
-Right?
-That's right.

660
00:53:48,384 --> 00:53:50,825
Let's go.
I'm sick of the people around here.

661
00:53:51,424 --> 00:53:52,904
Let's go over there.

662
00:53:52,984 --> 00:53:54,464
-Did she mean me?
-Yes.

663
00:54:01,864 --> 00:54:02,984
Nut.

664
00:54:05,464 --> 00:54:07,105
Did you bring me here

665
00:54:08,145 --> 00:54:09,665
for a particular reason?

666
00:54:14,185 --> 00:54:15,225
Look there.

667
00:54:16,904 --> 00:54:20,665
They are the same kind of orchid,
and yet they are different.

668
00:54:21,984 --> 00:54:23,464
Each flower is different.

669
00:54:28,585 --> 00:54:29,904
So are we.

670
00:54:31,864 --> 00:54:33,705
We all have value.

671
00:54:34,864 --> 00:54:36,345
There's no need to compare.

672
00:54:39,345 --> 00:54:41,745
Each of us is a unique flower.

673
00:54:47,025 --> 00:54:49,065
You are a special flower

674
00:54:50,904 --> 00:54:52,384
that belongs to me.

675
00:55:00,225 --> 00:55:01,944
Let's take some photos.

676
00:55:02,025 --> 00:55:03,384
I'll take lots of it.

677
00:55:03,464 --> 00:55:05,025
Okay.

678
00:55:13,225 --> 00:55:15,065
One, two, three.

679
00:55:24,025 --> 00:55:26,185
-Gen.
-What?

680
00:55:26,705 --> 00:55:28,065
Do you want some flowers?

681
00:55:28,745 --> 00:55:30,384
I will buy whatever you like.

682
00:55:30,984 --> 00:55:32,225
Which one do you like?

683
00:55:32,984 --> 00:55:34,384
Black-eyed Susan?

684
00:55:35,585 --> 00:55:37,065
Black-eyed Song sounds better.

685
00:55:38,944 --> 00:55:40,785
Let's just take more photos.

686
00:56:01,864 --> 00:56:03,345
What are you doing, Tofu?

687
00:56:04,504 --> 00:56:05,984
I'm choosing a photo.

688
00:56:06,665 --> 00:56:08,145
Which one do you like better?

689
00:56:09,305 --> 00:56:11,504
I'll post it on my Facebook.

690
00:56:11,984 --> 00:56:13,424
Save it as a good memory.

691
00:56:13,984 --> 00:56:15,025
Which ones?

692
00:56:15,105 --> 00:56:17,464
This one and this one too.

693
00:56:18,464 --> 00:56:20,025
I like this one.

694
00:56:20,105 --> 00:56:21,345
This?

695
00:56:21,424 --> 00:56:22,424
Yes.

696
00:56:23,345 --> 00:56:26,225
I want to post it too.
Can you send me that photo?

697
00:56:27,345 --> 00:56:28,424
Of course.

698
00:56:30,145 --> 00:56:31,504
In that case,

699
00:56:31,585 --> 00:56:34,665
I'll create a family group chat
and post the photos in there.

700
00:56:34,745 --> 00:56:36,585
So you can save photos from there.

701
00:56:53,984 --> 00:56:55,345
Yes, Juea.

702
00:56:55,424 --> 00:56:58,625
Nut, I'm sorry.
I need you to revise the script.

703
00:56:59,225 --> 00:57:01,225
I sent my comments to your email.

704
00:57:02,225 --> 00:57:03,625
I need it by tonight.

705
00:57:04,345 --> 00:57:05,785
Tonight?

706
00:57:05,864 --> 00:57:08,984
Yes. I was kind enough to let you go.

707
00:57:10,065 --> 00:57:11,105
I want it by tonight.

708
00:57:11,785 --> 00:57:12,864
All right.

709
00:57:16,105 --> 00:57:19,225
Juea is probably upset
that he has to shoot alone.

710
00:57:19,785 --> 00:57:20,785
Maybe.

711
00:57:24,585 --> 00:57:27,305
Well then, that's it for today.

712
00:57:27,825 --> 00:57:31,185
We should head back now.
Nut can also get some work done.

713
00:57:32,545 --> 00:57:35,705
Gen and I have to excuse ourselves.

714
00:57:35,785 --> 00:57:38,384
We are going to have dinner with my dad.

715
00:57:43,424 --> 00:57:47,265
I'm going to visit some more places.

716
00:57:47,864 --> 00:57:49,785
I want to find a good spot to sketch.

717
00:57:51,705 --> 00:57:53,504
I'll go with Prib then.

718
00:58:00,464 --> 00:58:02,944
You have to work.

719
00:58:03,585 --> 00:58:05,545
I won't be much help here.

720
00:58:06,665 --> 00:58:07,984
Hey.

721
00:58:08,065 --> 00:58:10,545
So you would rather go somewhere
than be with me?

722
00:58:12,065 --> 00:58:14,825
Nut, a little time alone won't kill you.

723
00:58:17,024 --> 00:58:18,145
All right, all right.

724
00:58:18,225 --> 00:58:19,345
You can go.

725
00:58:19,944 --> 00:58:21,585
Take care of yourself, okay?

726
00:58:22,705 --> 00:58:23,944
Look after Prib as well.

727
00:58:25,384 --> 00:58:27,384
I'm sure she'll be okay, though.

728
00:58:38,984 --> 00:58:42,105
You didn't just want
to hang out with me, did you?

729
00:59:42,904 --> 00:59:43,984
Tofu.

730
00:59:49,105 --> 00:59:50,145
Are you okay?

731
00:59:52,705 --> 00:59:54,504
I was a little overwhelmed.

732
00:59:55,345 --> 00:59:56,745
I just feel a bit dizzy.

733
01:00:00,825 --> 01:00:02,464
What happened to him?

734
01:00:05,745 --> 01:00:06,944
He was attacked.

735
01:00:07,424 --> 01:00:09,145
The police are investigating the case.

736
01:00:09,705 --> 01:00:12,625
I think he was involved
in some conflict of interest.

737
01:00:13,785 --> 01:00:17,024
He was a protest leader
in the Hollow Forest project.

738
01:00:27,825 --> 01:00:28,904
Tofu.

739
01:00:28,984 --> 01:00:32,145
I know you are confused right now.

740
01:00:32,225 --> 01:00:36,065
I didn't come here to pressure you
for an answer.

741
01:00:37,225 --> 01:00:38,944
I was just worried.

742
01:00:42,984 --> 01:00:46,944
I turned your trip
that should be filled with joy into this.

743
01:00:49,384 --> 01:00:52,345
It would be nice
if I could help you with something.

744
01:00:56,625 --> 01:00:58,225
I understand.

745
01:01:00,625 --> 01:01:02,305
I get it all,

746
01:01:05,384 --> 01:01:07,145
but it still hurts.

747
01:01:24,585 --> 01:01:28,384
Before this,
I had always wanted to meet Tatarn.

748
01:01:29,665 --> 01:01:31,625
At the same time,
I didn't want to see him,

749
01:01:32,424 --> 01:01:35,864
for fear that he might separate
Nut and me.

750
01:01:37,504 --> 01:01:39,585
Now, I want him to wake up,

751
01:01:40,265 --> 01:01:42,825
as he might hold the answer to my miracle.

752
01:01:44,185 --> 01:01:46,145
But if he doesn't wake up,

753
01:01:46,944 --> 01:01:49,424
I might be able to prolong my happiness.

754
01:01:50,464 --> 01:01:53,225
I still don't know
what will happen to me though.

755
01:01:56,504 --> 01:01:57,504
Tofu.

756
01:01:59,665 --> 01:02:01,305
Do you still want to hang out?

757
01:02:14,384 --> 01:02:16,504
I used to come here with Tarn.

758
01:02:17,105 --> 01:02:19,745
We both like art.

759
01:02:20,545 --> 01:02:24,345
It was around the time
he got back from Japan.

760
01:02:24,424 --> 01:02:26,864
He was getting involved
in political activities.

761
01:02:28,065 --> 01:02:30,665
He joined a workshop here.

762
01:02:32,185 --> 01:02:36,065
The way I saw it, Tarn was a warm person.

763
01:02:36,745 --> 01:02:38,904
But his paintings
were bursting with emotion.

764
01:02:39,545 --> 01:02:41,785
His paintings showed two men

765
01:02:41,864 --> 01:02:46,345
with satirical scenes about social
and political issues, the environment,

766
01:02:46,424 --> 01:02:49,785
religion, faith, and even love.

767
01:02:50,265 --> 01:02:52,265
He just took it all.

768
01:02:54,625 --> 01:02:58,984
I asked about the inspiration
behind these paintings.

769
01:02:59,904 --> 01:03:01,585
When something can't be said,

770
01:03:02,424 --> 01:03:04,145
then let art speak for you.

771
01:03:06,665 --> 01:03:09,904
Art is the most peaceful form
of expression.

772
01:03:11,585 --> 01:03:15,384
Its voice is subtle
and you need to interpret it.

773
01:03:16,265 --> 01:03:18,545
Yet it is a powerful way of communication.

774
01:03:20,864 --> 01:03:22,305
Too bad.

775
01:03:23,185 --> 01:03:25,424
Who would care about art

776
01:03:25,904 --> 01:03:27,745
when their stomachs are empty?

777
01:03:30,305 --> 01:03:31,904
That sounds depressing.

778
01:03:32,904 --> 01:03:34,225
Right?

779
01:03:34,944 --> 01:03:38,345
That's why Tarn and I studied art abroad.

780
01:03:40,424 --> 01:03:42,745
But you guys came back to do art here.

781
01:03:43,424 --> 01:03:45,864
That's because we're hopeful.

782
01:03:46,345 --> 01:03:47,944
Especially, Tarn.

783
01:03:48,665 --> 01:03:51,305
He wasn't just hopeful for art.

784
01:03:51,384 --> 01:03:53,024
He was hopeful for everything.

785
01:03:54,024 --> 01:03:58,065
He hoped for things
that are normal in other countries.

786
01:03:59,185 --> 01:04:03,105
He didn't want to see our country
destroyed and held back anymore.

787
01:04:04,145 --> 01:04:06,785
So he started the Hollow Forest,
something personal.

788
01:04:09,065 --> 01:04:11,185
I just want to live a normal life

789
01:04:11,265 --> 01:04:13,384
in a society where everything is normal.

790
01:04:14,024 --> 01:04:15,625
Everyone is equal.

791
01:04:16,585 --> 01:04:19,944
No matter your sexuality,
no one is seen as different.

792
01:04:42,024 --> 01:04:43,825
I used to wonder

793
01:04:43,904 --> 01:04:48,225
why he was so bold and true to himself.

794
01:04:49,984 --> 01:04:51,185
Why was that?

795
01:04:51,944 --> 01:04:54,145
It's because of his family, Tofu.

796
01:04:54,625 --> 01:04:56,904
He told me that before.

797
01:04:57,384 --> 01:04:59,944
He must have told Nut the same thing.

798
01:05:17,705 --> 01:05:19,065
Can I ask you something?

799
01:05:20,384 --> 01:05:22,464
How do you accept it so easily?

800
01:05:23,825 --> 01:05:25,504
That I like boys?

801
01:05:28,585 --> 01:05:30,944
Weren't you ever confused?

802
01:05:32,225 --> 01:05:33,585
Everyone is.

803
01:05:34,785 --> 01:05:36,544
I just knew myself early.

804
01:05:38,225 --> 01:05:40,225
When I told my parents about it,

805
01:05:41,544 --> 01:05:45,065
they even told me
that I didn't have to come out.

806
01:05:46,384 --> 01:05:48,345
Even though I'm their child,

807
01:05:48,904 --> 01:05:50,825
we are all human.

808
01:05:51,944 --> 01:05:53,585
My mother also said

809
01:05:54,265 --> 01:05:55,345
that gay

810
01:05:55,825 --> 01:05:58,105
also means joyful.

811
01:05:59,745 --> 01:06:01,145
Being gay is not wrong.

812
01:06:01,625 --> 01:06:04,105
We can have fun in our lives like others.

813
01:06:08,145 --> 01:06:10,864
Your parents are nice.

814
01:06:11,625 --> 01:06:12,625
Yes.

815
01:06:13,585 --> 01:06:15,225
My mother grew up abroad.

816
01:06:15,825 --> 01:06:19,544
My father, though he worked
for his Chinese family,

817
01:06:19,625 --> 01:06:21,984
later decided to start his own company.

818
01:06:23,345 --> 01:06:25,065
So I had some freedom.

819
01:06:30,145 --> 01:06:31,185
Unlike me.

820
01:06:32,464 --> 01:06:33,665
In my household…

821
01:06:35,065 --> 01:06:37,065
My parents would never understand.

822
01:06:41,585 --> 01:06:44,145
You don't need people to understand you.

823
01:06:45,424 --> 01:06:46,544
If telling them

824
01:06:47,504 --> 01:06:51,105
means being uncomfortable
or causing problems,

825
01:06:51,185 --> 01:06:52,305
then don't tell them.

826
01:06:53,145 --> 01:06:56,944
If telling them about it makes you happy,

827
01:06:57,745 --> 01:06:59,544
then tell them when you are ready.

828
01:07:01,944 --> 01:07:03,625
If I can prove myself to them,

829
01:07:04,904 --> 01:07:06,585
so that they accept me,

830
01:07:07,225 --> 01:07:08,745
-then--
-Why?

831
01:07:08,825 --> 01:07:13,145
Why should you struggle to be accepted
just because you are gay?

832
01:07:14,305 --> 01:07:16,265
Do gay men have to be good-looking,

833
01:07:16,345 --> 01:07:19,065
capable, and respectable

834
01:07:20,024 --> 01:07:21,185
to be accepted?

835
01:07:22,984 --> 01:07:27,065
Why can't they just accept us
as human beings?

836
01:07:37,345 --> 01:07:39,504
You have nothing to prove.

837
01:07:39,585 --> 01:07:42,384
You should just be yourself.

838
01:07:42,944 --> 01:07:44,944
Live the life you want to live.

839
01:07:47,345 --> 01:07:48,625
Got it?

840
01:08:20,945 --> 01:08:22,825
You didn't say you would bring a friend.

841
01:08:26,504 --> 01:08:28,784
He is not my friend.

842
01:08:32,305 --> 01:08:35,185
I see. You're one of the film crew, right?

843
01:08:35,825 --> 01:08:37,225
He looks older.

844
01:08:38,025 --> 01:08:39,584
I guess he's not your age.

845
01:08:43,784 --> 01:08:46,065
He is actually older than me.

846
01:08:46,905 --> 01:08:47,985
But…

847
01:08:48,464 --> 01:08:51,025
-Gen and I--
-Excuse me.

848
01:08:51,105 --> 01:08:52,664
We're still waiting for our food.

849
01:09:01,185 --> 01:09:04,865
Actually, Gen and I…

850
01:09:05,504 --> 01:09:06,384
We are…

851
01:09:07,784 --> 01:09:08,865
Oops!

852
01:09:08,945 --> 01:09:10,624
How clumsy of me.

853
01:09:10,704 --> 01:09:13,065
Excuse me. I spilled some water.

854
01:09:25,664 --> 01:09:27,025
Dad.

855
01:09:27,664 --> 01:09:29,985
So, Gen and I…

856
01:09:31,025 --> 01:09:32,384
We…

857
01:09:32,464 --> 01:09:33,464
are…

858
01:09:35,825 --> 01:09:38,584
How are you, Suwat? I'm good.

859
01:09:38,664 --> 01:09:40,225
Long time no see.

860
01:09:40,704 --> 01:09:43,185
What? Your kid got married?

861
01:09:43,945 --> 01:09:45,145
When?

862
01:09:45,225 --> 01:09:49,825
I can't believe your daughter
is old enough to even get married.

863
01:09:52,305 --> 01:09:56,105
My son is in his freshman year.
There's no hurry.

864
01:09:57,265 --> 01:09:59,305
Kids these days grow up fast.

865
01:09:59,784 --> 01:10:03,065
They are one thing today,
but tomorrow, they may change.

866
01:10:05,744 --> 01:10:08,585
I'm not that old. I can wait.

867
01:10:09,545 --> 01:10:11,145
I'll get a grandchild one day.

868
01:10:20,025 --> 01:10:21,865
You never gave him a hint?

869
01:10:24,825 --> 01:10:26,265
I wanted to tell him in one go.

870
01:10:27,624 --> 01:10:29,624
More like you plan to kill me
along with it.

871
01:10:33,025 --> 01:10:34,985
This is not how I thought it would go.

872
01:10:35,624 --> 01:10:38,825
My dad seems quite open-minded.

873
01:10:43,065 --> 01:10:46,345
Some parents are open-minded
about other people's kids.

874
01:10:47,145 --> 01:10:48,704
When it comes to their own child,

875
01:10:49,704 --> 01:10:51,305
they may be disappointed.

876
01:10:53,345 --> 01:10:54,905
Don't give up just yet.

877
01:10:54,985 --> 01:10:56,865
Let me talk to my dad first.

878
01:10:59,145 --> 01:11:00,945
Let's make him accept us.

879
01:11:01,025 --> 01:11:02,624
I won't give up.

880
01:11:02,704 --> 01:11:04,505
You won't give up either, right?

881
01:11:10,145 --> 01:11:12,425
How can I give up?

882
01:11:12,505 --> 01:11:14,225
You flirted with me first.

883
01:11:14,744 --> 01:11:16,585
And I'm confident

884
01:11:16,664 --> 01:11:18,425
that I'm good enough.

885
01:11:21,305 --> 01:11:24,065
What right does he have
to disapprove of me?

886
01:11:29,065 --> 01:11:31,265
If you think he really is open-minded,

887
01:11:32,865 --> 01:11:34,505
then we might have

888
01:11:35,505 --> 01:11:36,784
just caught him off guard.

889
01:11:38,545 --> 01:11:39,704
So we should just take it

890
01:11:40,704 --> 01:11:43,145
one step at a time

891
01:11:44,065 --> 01:11:45,624
until he gets used to it.

892
01:11:46,385 --> 01:11:48,065
Just like what you said to your fans.

893
01:11:56,185 --> 01:11:58,265
I'm glad I get to love you.

894
01:12:02,105 --> 01:12:03,624
There, there.

895
01:12:04,505 --> 01:12:06,065
You crybaby.

896
01:12:07,025 --> 01:12:08,265
Come here.

897
01:12:08,345 --> 01:12:09,865
I will console you.

898
01:12:11,385 --> 01:12:12,585
You want to console me?

899
01:12:13,624 --> 01:12:14,784
You got it.

900
01:12:15,385 --> 01:12:17,185
What are you doing?

901
01:12:17,265 --> 01:12:18,865
Song.

902
01:12:18,945 --> 01:12:21,145
No. Don't!

903
01:12:21,225 --> 01:12:22,225
No, Song!

904
01:12:34,825 --> 01:12:35,865
Come here.

905
01:12:37,065 --> 01:12:38,225
Here. Get this.

906
01:12:38,305 --> 01:12:41,265
-Here.
-Song, what's wrong with you?

907
01:12:41,985 --> 01:12:44,065
Stay in there.

908
01:12:50,185 --> 01:12:51,465
Hey.

909
01:12:51,545 --> 01:12:54,265
I'll get a new room and send you the bill.

910
01:12:55,865 --> 01:12:56,865
Don't!

911
01:12:58,865 --> 01:12:59,865
Don't.

912
01:12:59,945 --> 01:13:01,465
I was just

913
01:13:01,545 --> 01:13:02,945
fooling around with Song.

914
01:13:05,905 --> 01:13:07,025
You can leave now.

915
01:13:07,105 --> 01:13:08,704
See you tomorrow.

916
01:13:12,025 --> 01:13:13,704
Don't worry about it.

917
01:13:14,465 --> 01:13:15,945
We will get through this.

918
01:13:19,105 --> 01:13:21,664
I'll call you when I get to my room.

919
01:13:22,225 --> 01:13:23,825
All right. Go carefully.

920
01:13:24,585 --> 01:13:26,545
Go.

921
01:13:26,624 --> 01:13:29,225
Leave already.

922
01:13:36,145 --> 01:13:38,345
Do you want some too?

923
01:14:26,145 --> 01:14:27,385
When did you get back?

924
01:14:28,905 --> 01:14:31,145
You love your work more than me.

925
01:14:32,065 --> 01:14:33,585
I got back ages ago.

926
01:14:34,545 --> 01:14:36,025
You didn't even notice me.

927
01:14:36,585 --> 01:14:38,784
You chose going sightseeing over me.

928
01:14:39,425 --> 01:14:40,624
Now, we are even.

929
01:14:43,305 --> 01:14:44,624
Isn't it boring

930
01:14:45,105 --> 01:14:47,305
having to work while on a vacation?

931
01:14:48,865 --> 01:14:50,065
I'm used to it.

932
01:14:51,945 --> 01:14:53,465
But I'm not.

933
01:14:55,025 --> 01:14:57,265
You keep checking your phone.

934
01:14:57,345 --> 01:15:00,425
You don't have enough time
to eat or sleep.

935
01:15:00,505 --> 01:15:02,585
You don't get any exercise.

936
01:15:02,664 --> 01:15:05,225
And not to mention the benefits,
there's none.

937
01:15:05,784 --> 01:15:08,624
When the show was on-air,
you still took all the criticism.

938
01:15:09,265 --> 01:15:11,784
I know how much you love your work.

939
01:15:13,905 --> 01:15:14,945
What's up with you?

940
01:15:15,505 --> 01:15:17,065
You're being weird lately.

941
01:15:20,784 --> 01:15:22,744
I'm worried about you.

942
01:15:31,025 --> 01:15:32,065
I know

943
01:15:32,784 --> 01:15:35,185
how much you love this job.

944
01:15:38,225 --> 01:15:39,985
Are you really okay with it?

945
01:15:42,265 --> 01:15:43,305
Of course, I am.

946
01:15:44,945 --> 01:15:48,624
I knew doing this job
in a country like this wouldn't be easy.

947
01:15:50,065 --> 01:15:51,065
At first,

948
01:15:51,145 --> 01:15:53,265
I just liked writing

949
01:15:53,824 --> 01:15:55,425
as my dad didn't let me do much.

950
01:15:56,624 --> 01:15:58,505
Once I got to do it as a job though,

951
01:15:59,784 --> 01:16:01,145
I found out

952
01:16:01,744 --> 01:16:05,065
that writing can heal me.

953
01:16:06,145 --> 01:16:10,704
It enables me to express
what I can't say directly.

954
01:16:13,025 --> 01:16:14,824
Whenever I'm exhausted

955
01:16:15,585 --> 01:16:16,865
or I feel like giving up,

956
01:16:19,065 --> 01:16:23,624
I look back to the day
that I chose this path.

957
01:17:30,624 --> 01:17:33,744
Can you guess
which scene I liked the most?

958
01:17:36,185 --> 01:17:37,664
The CGI one?

959
01:17:38,185 --> 01:17:39,585
You know me well.

960
01:17:39,664 --> 01:17:42,065
The CGI scene is so seamless
and beautiful. I love it.

961
01:17:42,784 --> 01:17:45,425
Now, I will try to guess
which scene you like?

962
01:17:46,945 --> 01:17:48,585
Which one do you think I liked?

963
01:17:51,145 --> 01:17:52,385
The ending.

964
01:17:54,225 --> 01:17:55,465
How did you know?

965
01:17:55,945 --> 01:17:57,465
Because I know you.

966
01:17:57,545 --> 01:17:58,865
I wanted to know

967
01:17:58,945 --> 01:18:00,225
at the end,

968
01:18:00,824 --> 01:18:03,065
if the character has to choose one way,

969
01:18:03,145 --> 01:18:04,425
what is it going to be like?

970
01:18:05,985 --> 01:18:07,345
If you really want to know,

971
01:18:08,265 --> 01:18:09,905
why don't you write your own ending?

972
01:18:12,784 --> 01:18:14,465
Do you really think I could do it?

973
01:18:18,624 --> 01:18:21,704
If you like it, then give it a try.

974
01:18:25,865 --> 01:18:27,784
My parents wouldn't like it.

975
01:18:28,905 --> 01:18:30,624
If you're doing what you love,

976
01:18:31,185 --> 01:18:33,105
why wouldn't they like it?

977
01:18:34,945 --> 01:18:36,385
I believe in you.

978
01:18:38,865 --> 01:18:40,425
I'm looking forward to seeing it.

979
01:18:45,704 --> 01:18:47,624
I still remember that feeling.

980
01:18:48,385 --> 01:18:49,865
It's like falling in love.

981
01:18:50,505 --> 01:18:52,145
It's like you finally found someone.

982
01:18:53,225 --> 01:18:55,545
I'm lucky to have found what I like early.

983
01:18:56,824 --> 01:18:58,664
Though along the way,

984
01:18:58,744 --> 01:19:00,265
it wasn't easy at all.

985
01:19:02,784 --> 01:19:03,784
Nut.

986
01:19:07,985 --> 01:19:08,985
What's wrong?

987
01:19:11,865 --> 01:19:14,425
I didn't get in the short story contest.

988
01:19:16,145 --> 01:19:17,905
I didn't get a prize.

989
01:19:19,225 --> 01:19:22,065
Were you confident that you would win?

990
01:19:24,065 --> 01:19:25,345
Of course, I was.

991
01:19:25,985 --> 01:19:28,225
I put a lot of effort into it.

992
01:19:28,824 --> 01:19:31,345
I thought I might win something, at least.

993
01:19:33,744 --> 01:19:35,704
Writing is like art.

994
01:19:36,425 --> 01:19:37,905
There's no right and wrong.

995
01:19:38,585 --> 01:19:39,585
When you turn it in,

996
01:19:40,145 --> 01:19:42,265
it's a matter of what the judges like.

997
01:19:43,345 --> 01:19:44,585
Don't forget

998
01:19:45,345 --> 01:19:47,865
that art serves no one

999
01:19:48,505 --> 01:19:50,545
and it is a slave to none.

1000
01:19:51,345 --> 01:19:52,465
Therefore,

1001
01:19:53,345 --> 01:19:55,784
I don't want you to pressure yourself
just to win.

1002
01:19:56,744 --> 01:19:58,145
It is okay to lose.

1003
01:19:58,624 --> 01:20:00,624
Whether you make it or not is fine.

1004
01:20:01,185 --> 01:20:02,905
Along the way,

1005
01:20:03,784 --> 01:20:05,545
I hope you are happy with it.

1006
01:20:08,545 --> 01:20:10,505
But happiness won't feed you.

1007
01:20:11,664 --> 01:20:14,065
I wanted the prize money
to pay for my tuition,

1008
01:20:14,985 --> 01:20:16,985
in case I have to support myself

1009
01:20:18,345 --> 01:20:20,145
when I go to college.

1010
01:20:22,025 --> 01:20:23,704
You can try again.

1011
01:20:24,385 --> 01:20:27,265
Gain more experience by trial and error.

1012
01:20:30,145 --> 01:20:31,225
I believe that

1013
01:20:32,185 --> 01:20:34,945
one day, someone will like your work.

1014
01:20:37,505 --> 01:20:40,345
You've got this. I'm here for you.

1015
01:20:45,704 --> 01:20:49,865
Juea really likes your work.

1016
01:20:53,465 --> 01:20:54,505
So…

1017
01:20:55,905 --> 01:20:58,585
did you work with Juea from the beginning?

1018
01:21:01,225 --> 01:21:03,185
Juea and I get along.

1019
01:21:03,704 --> 01:21:05,105
So working together is easy.

1020
01:21:06,065 --> 01:21:08,065
Still, I can't say that I'm successful.

1021
01:21:10,425 --> 01:21:11,865
But if I keep going,

1022
01:21:13,345 --> 01:21:15,664
I can still write what I want to say.

1023
01:21:19,704 --> 01:21:21,624
What do you want to tell people

1024
01:21:23,545 --> 01:21:25,185
from the story you are working on?

1025
01:21:29,265 --> 01:21:30,704
I want to tell them

1026
01:21:31,345 --> 01:21:33,744
that the country that exports shows
about boys' love,

1027
01:21:34,664 --> 01:21:36,624
has the prettiest transgender people,

1028
01:21:37,985 --> 01:21:39,784
and has gay couples as net idols,

1029
01:21:40,744 --> 01:21:42,824
doesn't support the rights
for those people,

1030
01:21:43,865 --> 01:21:46,305
as they aren't truly accepted there.

1031
01:21:52,065 --> 01:21:54,185
I also want to tell him

1032
01:21:57,265 --> 01:21:59,545
that even though it has been a decade,

1033
01:22:01,185 --> 01:22:02,905
I still want to apologize,

1034
01:22:05,265 --> 01:22:06,664
and express my gratitude.

1035
01:22:10,305 --> 01:22:12,145
He is a good memory,

1036
01:22:14,545 --> 01:22:16,945
an inspiration that made me who I am,

1037
01:22:19,385 --> 01:22:21,105
and the one who made me love myself.

1038
01:22:26,865 --> 01:22:28,065
Then…

1039
01:22:28,784 --> 01:22:31,945
your show should have
a happy ending, right?

1040
01:22:34,744 --> 01:22:37,905
Hey. Are you jealous of my work now?

1041
01:22:40,905 --> 01:22:42,505
I'm just curious.

1042
01:22:43,585 --> 01:22:46,585
Don't forget that I'm a fan of your work,

1043
01:22:47,425 --> 01:22:49,105
and a fan of yours.

1044
01:22:52,145 --> 01:22:54,145
It will have a bad ending like my life.

1045
01:22:55,985 --> 01:22:57,905
I don't want to turn back time.

1046
01:22:57,985 --> 01:22:59,145
I want to move forward.

1047
01:23:02,345 --> 01:23:03,985
And don't make me tell you

1048
01:23:04,624 --> 01:23:06,545
who…

1049
01:23:08,265 --> 01:23:09,345
keeps me going.

1050
01:23:56,065 --> 01:23:57,905
Nut and Tatarn

1051
01:23:58,505 --> 01:24:01,585
reminded me of a quote
from a book that I read.

1052
01:24:02,664 --> 01:24:04,145
It said,

1053
01:24:04,784 --> 01:24:07,905
"Good love makes us want to grow
into a better person,

1054
01:24:08,865 --> 01:24:11,865
and makes us love ourselves more
as we love that person."

1055
01:24:14,065 --> 01:24:16,425
Nut is who he is today

1056
01:24:16,505 --> 01:24:18,545
as a result of Tatarn's love.

1057
01:24:19,664 --> 01:24:20,784
Therefore,

1058
01:24:21,265 --> 01:24:23,985
at such a critical time for Tatarn,

1059
01:24:24,985 --> 01:24:27,185
if Nut can help him,

1060
01:24:28,185 --> 01:24:29,744
then I should be glad.

1061
01:24:30,945 --> 01:24:32,105
Right?

1062
01:24:51,664 --> 01:24:53,065
Didn't you get any sleep?

1063
01:24:54,704 --> 01:24:55,985
Are you all right?

1064
01:24:57,385 --> 01:24:59,824
A lot of strange things
have been happening lately.

1065
01:25:03,065 --> 01:25:04,945
I'm beginning to see some images.

1066
01:25:07,784 --> 01:25:09,265
There was a place.

1067
01:25:11,585 --> 01:25:12,664
There was a person.

1068
01:25:17,505 --> 01:25:19,065
Are you regaining your memory?

1069
01:25:21,545 --> 01:25:23,185
I'm not sure about it.

1070
01:25:28,784 --> 01:25:30,664
Let's go to the doctor.

1071
01:25:32,505 --> 01:25:34,265
I don't want to remember it.

1072
01:25:37,385 --> 01:25:38,585
I'm afraid,

1073
01:25:41,505 --> 01:25:43,185
but also curious.

1074
01:25:46,025 --> 01:25:47,185
Tofu.

1075
01:25:52,624 --> 01:25:53,784
It's okay.

1076
01:25:55,225 --> 01:25:56,744
I will be here for you.

1077
01:26:03,145 --> 01:26:04,265
Nut.

1078
01:26:06,744 --> 01:26:09,225
The real reason
I brought you to Chiang Mai

1079
01:26:11,744 --> 01:26:13,704
is that I saw an image of a man

1080
01:26:16,065 --> 01:26:17,065
here.

1081
01:26:20,784 --> 01:26:22,585
So, did you used to live here?

1082
01:26:24,824 --> 01:26:26,305
I don't know.

1083
01:26:30,585 --> 01:26:32,585
Can we go somewhere?

1084
01:26:35,225 --> 01:26:36,265
Being there,

1085
01:26:37,784 --> 01:26:40,065
I might find out the truth.

1086
01:26:57,345 --> 01:26:58,345
Tofu.

1087
01:26:59,985 --> 01:27:01,145
Are you scared?

1088
01:27:04,545 --> 01:27:05,824
I don't know…

1089
01:27:07,065 --> 01:27:09,065
what will happen to me

1090
01:27:11,345 --> 01:27:12,905
if I take you to see him.

1091
01:27:14,864 --> 01:27:17,744
We will finally get to know who you are.

1092
01:27:34,784 --> 01:27:36,985
You're afraid
that we can't be together, right?

1093
01:27:40,425 --> 01:27:41,425
That's right.

1094
01:27:49,704 --> 01:27:51,824
If he's really someone in your family,

1095
01:27:52,864 --> 01:27:54,465
we can talk to him

1096
01:27:54,545 --> 01:27:56,585
and ask if you can stay with us.

1097
01:27:57,145 --> 01:27:59,704
My mother and I don't look like
bad people, do we?

1098
01:28:02,505 --> 01:28:05,585
Why did you bring us to the hospital?

1099
01:28:07,025 --> 01:28:10,784
Tofu's cousin may be a doctor,
like your mom.

1100
01:28:11,345 --> 01:28:12,465
Am I right?

1101
01:28:14,744 --> 01:28:16,065
Is he sick?

1102
01:28:18,425 --> 01:28:20,704
Why is the person you saw in the hospital?

1103
01:28:20,784 --> 01:28:22,145
Who is he?

1104
01:29:25,185 --> 01:29:26,465
Tarn.

1105
01:29:43,425 --> 01:29:45,465
Is that Tarn, Neung's friend?

1106
01:29:57,465 --> 01:29:59,465
The person you remembered is Tarn?

1107
01:30:12,505 --> 01:30:14,905
I was scared that if I brought you to him,

1108
01:30:16,824 --> 01:30:18,664
I would lose you.

1109
01:30:21,545 --> 01:30:25,025
Na must be really happy that her son…

1110
01:30:26,025 --> 01:30:28,185
Everybody has a gender.

1111
01:30:28,265 --> 01:30:30,585
You can be any gender you wish to be.

1112
01:30:31,145 --> 01:30:33,624
And every gender is equal.

1113
01:30:34,624 --> 01:30:36,185
I'm glad you can be yourself

1114
01:30:36,985 --> 01:30:39,145
whenever you are with me.

1115
01:30:41,185 --> 01:30:43,025
If something is troubling you,

1116
01:30:43,585 --> 01:30:45,345
I'll be the one to ease your mind.

